00:14:58,920 --> 00:14:59,920
Not this kind.
不是这种。

321
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:03,280
They've got weird names like ganache and praline.
它们有像甘纳许和果仁糖这样奇怪的名字。

322
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:06,680
Look, I just saw someone walking around inside.
看，我刚才看到有人在里面走动。

323
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,680
These people are being very rude.
这些人非常无礼。

324
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:10,480
Finally, someone's coming.
终于有人来了。

325
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,400
They don't look too happy.
他们看起来不太高兴。

326
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,400
Hi, sir.
你好，先生。

327
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,960
Would you like to sponsor us or make a donation to...
您愿意赞助我们或捐款给……

328
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,520
What grade are you kids in?
你们这些孩子上几年级了？

329
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:18,520
Grade 7.
七年级。

330
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:21,680
Then for goodness sake, don't you see this sign?
看在老天爷的份上，你们没看到这个牌子吗？

331
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:22,680
Can't you read?
你们不识字吗？

332
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:23,680
No soliciting?
禁止推销？

333
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:33,560
All right, so door-to-door salesman.
好吧，所以是上门推销员。

334
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:37,080
I think this used to be a very American thing.
我觉得这曾经是很美国化的事情。

335
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:42,440
I think back in the 50s, you would always see movies where this was actually a profession.
我想在50年代，你总能在电影里看到这其实是一种职业。

336
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,440
That's right.
没错。

337
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:50,680
People would go door-to-door selling hairbrushes or magazine subscriptions, pretty much everything.
人们会挨家挨户卖发刷或杂志订阅，几乎什么都卖。

338
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:53,000
Yeah, you still see it sometimes.
是啊，现在有时还能看到。

339
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:59,960
Some people sell insurance or there are a lot of religious door-to-door salespeople
有些人卖保险，或者有很多宗教上门推销员，

340
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:03,200
who want to sell religious books or magazines.
他们想卖宗教书籍或杂志。

341
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:07,120
But I think it was much more popular in the 1950s because people didn't really use their
但我认为这在50年代更流行，因为那时人们不太用

342
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:09,000
phones as much to sell things.
电话来卖东西。

343
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:12,480
It was cheaper to have someone drive his car to your neighborhood and then go to every
雇人开车到你的社区，然后挨家挨户

344
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,480
single house.
推销更便宜。

345
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:16,720
But yeah, it's a very interesting job.
不过，这确实是个很有趣的工作。

346
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,240
I think it'd be very lonely.
我觉得会很孤独。

347
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:22,680
And also, I think, well, now maybe that's been reduced a lot because now you have the
而且，我想，现在可能已经减少了很多，因为现在有了

348
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:23,680
internet.
互联网。

349
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:28,320
Oh yeah, well the internet means that the salespeople come to you without you having
哦对，互联网意味着推销员不用你

350
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,880
to get up.
起身就能找上门。

351
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:34,720
So basically, you're sitting at home in your pajamas and you can order a TV and some clothes.
所以基本上，你穿着睡衣坐在家里，就能订一台电视和一些衣服。

352
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:39,200
But it's very interesting because I remember you would have all these door-to-door salesmen.
但这很有趣，因为我记得以前有很多上门推销员。

353
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:43,080
For example, I had one visit me once who was selling me encyclopedias.
比如，有一次有个人来向我推销百科全书。

354
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,080
Really?
真的吗？

355
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:48,000
A big collection of like, I don't know, 37 books or more.
一大套，大概有37本书或更多。

356
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,640
It was a huge amount of books, encyclopedias.
那是很大一堆书，百科全书。

357
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:52,160
And I don't know if you see that anymore.
我不知道现在还能不能看到这个。

358
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:54,000
Not really, not in the States.
不太常见了，在美国不是。

359
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:58,480
I don't know if anyone buys physical, huge encyclopedias to have in their home.
我不知道还有没有人买实体的大部头百科全书放在家里。

360
00:16:58,480 --> 00:17:00,320
No, only collectors perhaps.
没有，可能只有收藏家会买。

361
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,320
Maybe.
也许吧。

362
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,320
So it's a very interesting profession.
所以这是个很有趣的职业。

363
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:06,200
I don't know, in the United States, as you say, it's not very common anymore.
我不知道，在美国，就像你说的，现在已经不常见了。

364
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,800
Very little, maybe specific services.
非常少，可能只有特定的服务。

365
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:09,800
But this is interesting.
但这很有意思。

366
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:11,760
Maybe in your country, this is still a big thing.
也许在你的国家，这还是很普遍的事。

367
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:12,800
Yeah, let us know.
是啊，告诉我们吧。

368
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:16,600
In your country, are door-to-door salespeople still common?
在你的国家，上门推销员还常见吗？

369
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,640
Do you see them?
你见过他们吗？

370
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,200
Our website is EnglishPod.com.
我们的网站是EnglishPod.com。

371
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,200
We hope to see you there.
我们希望能在那里见到你。

372
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,200
All right, bye-bye.
好了，再见。

373
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:28,720
Bye-bye.
再见。
